result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (2nd) and Operating w/ PAC (2nd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (2nd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (2nd) was dismissed by the court.

  • James Donald Daczyk was found guilty of OWI (2nd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • James Donald Daczyk was found guilty of 2nd-Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.30(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses outright Count 2 and repeater enhancer on Count 3. Court dismisses and reads-in Count 4. Sentencing argument by ADA Anderson. Sentencing argument by Attorney Sanders-Brown. Statement by the defendant. Court sentences the defendant to: COUNT 1- 25 days WCJ, concurrent to any existing sentence. $1,379.00 fine inclusive of costs, $42.50 Blood Draw Costs, to be paid up to 25% of inmate earnings. 12 month DL revocation, 12 mo IID, OWI assessment. COUNT 3- SWD and places on probation for a period of 2 years. Consecutive to any sentence currently serving in Winnebago County case 11CF48. CONDITIONS: Absolute Sobriety, No Bars. Not to possess any imparing substances without a valid prescription. No Contact with Troy Woodrow and/or Jason Steele. Court leaves No Contact with Michelle Hoeft up to supervising agent. Terms of Agent. Costs of matter to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Appeal Rights Given.
